"create_before_destroy absolutely achieves zero downtime because ALB always has healthy targets throughout the update.
 But it does NOT prevent mixed versions — old and new EC2s serve traffic together briefly during the update.
 Zero downtime and zero mixed versions are two different problems.
 create_before_destroy solves downtime.
 Blue/Green and Canary solve mixed versions." ✅

NORMALLY IN AWS CONSOLE for Canary
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Step 1 → go to EC2 Console
          → Load Balancers
          → select your ALB
          → Listeners tab
          → click View/edit rules


Step 2 → edit the listener rule
          → click edit on forward action
          → you will see this:

          Target Group        Weight
          ─────────────────────────
          TG-old              100
          TG-new              0

          change to:
          TG-old              95
          TG-new              5
          → Save ✅


Step 3 → monitor
          → CloudWatch metrics
          → check error rate
          → check response time
          → check logs


Step 4 → increase weight again in console
          TG-old  75
          TG-new  25
          → Save ✅

Step 5 → keep increasing
          TG-old  50  TG-new  50  → Save
          TG-old  25  TG-new  75  → Save
          TG-old  0   TG-new  100 → Save ✅

