BOTH Blue/Green and Canary USE SAME ALB WEIGHT FEATURE
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

ALB Listener Rule → Forward Action → Target Group Weights

this is the SAME feature
difference is only HOW you use the weights


BLUE/GREEN — weight as a SWITCH
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

before:
  TG-Blue   weight = 100  ✅ live
  TG-Green  weight = 0    🔄 testing

after testing green:
  TG-Blue   weight = 0    ❌ off
  TG-Green  weight = 100  ✅ live

pattern:  100/0  →  0/100
          ON/OFF     OFF/ON
          no steps in between
          instant full switch


CANARY — weight as a DIAL
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  TG-Old  weight = 100  TG-New weight = 0
  TG-Old  weight = 95   TG-New weight = 5
  TG-Old  weight = 75   TG-New weight = 25
  TG-Old  weight = 50   TG-New weight = 50
  TG-Old  weight = 25   TG-New weight = 75
  TG-Old  weight = 0    TG-New weight = 100

pattern:  gradual steps
          monitor at each step
          full control


